🚢 Titanic 2 

A century after the real-life disaster and over 25 years after James Cameron’s Titanic broke box office records, a new generation is about to experience the legendary romance and tragedy — this time with a fresh twist. Rumor has it that a reimagined version of Titanic is in the works, with Timothée Chalamet and Zendaya set to star as star-crossed lovers aboard the ill-fated ship.

The project, tentatively titled Titanic, is said to be less of a straight remake and more of a “reinterpretation” — blending historical drama, romance, and a modern narrative structure designed to resonate with younger audiences while honoring the grandeur of the original film.

Insiders claim that this new Titanic will weave together two timelines: the doomed 1912 voyage and a present-day investigation by a young historian (played by Zendaya) uncovering a mysterious diary linked to a passenger named Jack Dawson — here reimagined and played by Timothée Chalamet.

Feel free to express your thoughts on this exciting project by leaving a comment below.

A century after the real-life disaster and over 25 years after James Cameron’s Titanic broke box office records, a new generation is about to experience the legendary romance and tragedy — this time with a fresh twist. Rumor has it that a reimagined version of Titanic is in the works, with Timothée Chalamet and Zendaya set to star as star-crossed lovers aboard the ill-fated ship.

The project, tentatively titled Titanic, is said to be less of a straight remake and more of a “reinterpretation” — blending historical drama, romance, and a modern narrative structure designed to resonate with younger audiences while honoring the grandeur of the original film.

Insiders claim that this new Titanic will weave together two timelines: the doomed 1912 voyage and a present-day investigation by a young historian (played by Zendaya) uncovering a mysterious diary linked to a passenger named Jack Dawson — here reimagined and played by Timothée Chalamet.

Feel free to express your thoughts on this exciting project by leaving a comment below.

snippet.title: Here With Us - Dunsin Oyekan
snippet.description:
When Jacob met with God in Genesis 28, he said “Surely the LORD is in this place, and I did not know it.” 

Most times when we gather to worship, most people are not fully cognizant of where we have come to. That is why the writer of Hebrews said “But you have come to Mount Zion and to the city of the living God, the heavenly Jerusalem, to an innumerable company of angels, to the general assembly and church of the firstborn who are registered in heaven, to God the Judge of all, to the spirits of just men made perfect, to Jesus the Mediator of the new covenant, and to the blood of sprinkling that speaks better things than that of Abel. Hebrews 12:22-24 

When we realise where we have come to, our response to the atmosphere will be different and appropriate. Whenever we gather as believers, we must be aware of God’s divine Presence and must take advantage of His Presence.

So “Why did we come if we don’t see Him?” As we worship, we have come to GOD so we MUST SEE HIM!
